  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "description": "A meld is a valid combination of cards grouped and revealed as a scoring or action unit in a card game. The two most common meld types are sets (three or more cards of the same rank — three kings, four sevens) and runs (three or more cards of the same suit in consecutive rank order — 5-6-7 of hearts). Rummy-family games are built around melding: the goal is to arrange your hand into valid melds and declare them.\n",
